### Kita Library API - Sample Requests
### Use with VS Code REST Client extension or IntelliJ HTTP Client

### =============================================================
### Environment Setup (configure these variables)
### =============================================================

@base_identity = http://localhost:3000
@base_book = http://localhost:3001
@base_transaction = http://localhost:3002
@internal_token = dev-internal-token
@access_token = {{login.response.body.data.access_token}}
@refresh_token = {{login.response.body.data.refresh_token}}

### =============================================================
### Identity Service
### =============================================================

### Health Check
GET {{base_identity}}/api/v1/health

### Readiness Check
GET {{base_identity}}/api/v1/ready

### Register User
POST {{base_identity}}/api/v1/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "full_name": "Demo User",
  "email": "demo@example.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

### Login (Password Grant)
# @name login
POST {{base_identity}}/api/v1/auth/token
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded

grant_type=password&email=demo@example.com&password=password123

### Refresh Token
POST {{base_identity}}/api/v1/auth/token
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded

grant_type=refresh_token&refresh_token={{refresh_token}}

### Logout
POST {{base_identity}}/api/v1/auth/logout
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "refresh_token": "{{refresh_token}}"
}

### Get Profile
GET {{base_identity}}/api/v1/users/me
Authorization: Bearer {{access_token}}

### =============================================================
### Book Service
### =============================================================

### Health Check
GET {{base_book}}/api/v1/health

### List Books (with pagination and search)
GET {{base_book}}/api/v1/books?page=1&per_page=5

### List Books (search by keyword)
GET {{base_book}}/api/v1/books?search=filsafat

### List Books (filter by category)
GET {{base_book}}/api/v1/books?category=Fiksi

### Get Book Detail
GET {{base_book}}/api/v1/books/{{book_id}}

### Check Book Availability
GET {{base_book}}/api/v1/books/{{book_id}}/availability

### Create Book (Internal Token Required)
POST {{base_book}}/api/v1/books
Content-Type: application/json
X-Internal-Token: {{internal_token}}

{
  "isbn": "978-602-00-0001-1",
  "title": "Sample Book",
  "author": "Sample Author",
  "publisher": "Sample Publisher",
  "category": "Fiksi",
  "description": "A sample book for testing",
  "total_stock": 5
}

### Update Book (Internal Token Required)
PUT {{base_book}}/api/v1/books/{{book_id}}
Content-Type: application/json
X-Internal-Token: {{internal_token}}

{
  "title": "Updated Book Title",
  "author": "Updated Author"
}

### Internal: Decrease Stock
POST {{base_book}}/api/v1/internal/books/{{book_id}}/stock/decrease
Content-Type: application/json
X-Internal-Token: {{internal_token}}

{
  "quantity": 1,
  "transaction_id": "test-txn-id"
}

### Internal: Increase Stock
POST {{base_book}}/api/v1/internal/books/{{book_id}}/stock/increase
Content-Type: application/json
X-Internal-Token: {{internal_token}}

{
  "quantity": 1,
  "transaction_id": "test-txn-id"
}

### =============================================================
### Transaction Service
### =============================================================

### Health Check
GET {{base_transaction}}/api/v1/health

### Borrow a Book
### Note: borrow is processed asynchronously. Returns HTTP 202 Accepted. The response status will be PENDING.
### Poll GET /api/v1/transactions/{id} until the status becomes ACTIVE or CANCELLED.
POST {{base_transaction}}/api/v1/transactions/borrow
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{access_token}}

{
  "book_id": "{{book_id}}",
  "idempotency_key": "uuid-generated-by-client"
}

### Get Active Loans
GET {{base_transaction}}/api/v1/transactions/active
Authorization: Bearer {{access_token}}

### Get Transaction Detail (use this to poll final borrow/return status)
GET {{base_transaction}}/api/v1/transactions/{{transaction_id}}
Authorization: Bearer {{access_token}}

### Return a Book
### Note: return is processed asynchronously. Returns HTTP 202 Accepted. The response status will be RETURN_PENDING.
### Poll GET /api/v1/transactions/{id} until the status becomes RETURNED, RETURNED_LATE, or ACTIVE if the return is rejected.
POST {{base_transaction}}/api/v1/transactions/{{transaction_id}}/return
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{access_token}}

{
  "idempotency_key": "uuid-generated-by-client-for-return"
}

### Get Transaction History
GET {{base_transaction}}/api/v1/transactions/history?page=1&per_page=10
Authorization: Bearer {{access_token}}

### =============================================================
### Error Cases (for testing)
### =============================================================

### Try borrowing without JWT
POST {{base_transaction}}/api/v1/transactions/borrow
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "book_id": "some-id"
}

### Try borrowing with invalid book ID
POST {{base_transaction}}/api/v1/transactions/borrow
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{access_token}}

{
  "book_id": "00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000"
}

### Try returning another user's transaction
POST {{base_transaction}}/api/v1/transactions/{{transaction_id}}/return
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9.eyJ1c2VyX2lkIjoib3RoZXItdXNlciIsImVtYWlsIjoib3RoZXJAZXhhbXBsZS5jb20iLCJyb2xlIjoiTUVNQkVSIiwiaXNzIjoia2l0YS1pZGVudGl0eS1zZXJ2aWNlIn0.test

{
  "idempotency_key": "uuid-generated-by-client-for-return"
}
